{
  "video_id": "HljoFTfcO_E",
  "title": "Chapter 4 - Income Statement EXPLAINED!",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 3490.0,
      "end_time": 4880.0,
      "text": "Hi, Else here."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 4880.0,
      "end_time": 7850.0,
      "text": "And in this video, we&#39;ll be exploring financial statements,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 7850.0,
      "end_time": 10610.0,
      "text": "what they look like, and how they interconnect."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 10610.0,
      "end_time": 13420.0,
      "text": "Why are financial statements necessary?"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 13420.0,
      "end_time": 16900.0,
      "text": "Financial statements tell a business&#39; story, what it does,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 16900.0,
      "end_time": 18740.0,
      "text": "and how well it does it."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 18740.0,
      "end_time": 21190.0,
      "text": "They provide a business&#39; financial performance,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 21190.0,
      "end_time": 24460.0,
      "text": "its current financial position, and its cash flows."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 24460.0,
      "end_time": 27140.0,
      "text": "Both internal and external stakeholders"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 27140.0,
      "end_time": 30380.0,
      "text": "use the financial statements to analyze the business and answer"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 30380.0,
      "end_time": 31620.0,
      "text": "questions."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 31620.0,
      "end_time": 33410.0,
      "text": "That allows them to make decisions"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 33410.0,
      "end_time": 35400.0,
      "text": "and meet their objectives."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 35400.0,
      "end_time": 38490.0,
      "text": "A business will produce the following financial statements,"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 38490.0,
      "end_time": 41020.0,
      "text": "income statement, statement of retained earnings,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 41020.0,
      "end_time": 43930.0,
      "text": "balance sheet, and the statement of cash flows."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 43930.0,
      "end_time": 46560.0,
      "text": "Statements must be completed in a specific order."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 46560.0,
      "end_time": 50440.0,
      "text": "And we&#39;ll start with the income statement."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 50440.0,
      "end_time": 52700.0,
      "text": "An income statement reports the results"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 52700.0,
      "end_time": 54830.0,
      "text": "of a business&#39; day-to-day operations,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 54830.0,
      "end_time": 57140.0,
      "text": "the revenues, less expenses incurred"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 57140.0,
      "end_time": 61090.0,
      "text": "to generate that revenue, to obtain a total profit."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 61090.0,
      "end_time": 63730.0,
      "text": "The income statement measures a business&#39; performance"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 63730.0,
      "end_time": 67150.0,
      "text": "within a period of time, either annually, quarterly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 67150.0,
      "end_time": 68630.0,
      "text": "or monthly."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 68630.0,
      "end_time": 70590.0,
      "text": "To better understand the income statement,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 70590.0,
      "end_time": 74070.0,
      "text": "we have to understand the two main elements, revenues"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 74070.0,
      "end_time": 76090.0,
      "text": "and expenses."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 76090.0,
      "end_time": 79550.0,
      "text": "Revenues are the income a business earns."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 79550.0,
      "end_time": 82050.0,
      "text": "There are only two ways to earn revenue."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 82050.0,
      "end_time": 85370.0,
      "text": "Businesses either provide a service or a good."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 85370.0,
      "end_time": 88400.0,
      "text": "The key to revenue is that it must be earned."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 88400.0,
      "end_time": 90010.0,
      "text": "What does that mean?"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 90010.0,
      "end_time": 94480.0,
      "text": "It means that the business has done their job-- past tense."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 94480.0,
      "end_time": 97070.0,
      "text": "For example, if a lawn care business"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 97070.0,
      "end_time": 99500.0,
      "text": "plans to mow a customer&#39;s lawn tomorrow,"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 99500.0,
      "end_time": 103310.0,
      "text": "that is not earned revenue today because they have not"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 103310.0,
      "end_time": 105130.0,
      "text": "done their job yet."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 105130.0,
      "end_time": 107470.0,
      "text": "After they&#39;ve finished mowing the customer&#39;s lawn,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 107470.0,
      "end_time": 109760.0,
      "text": "they have earned their revenue."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 109760.0,
      "end_time": 112850.0,
      "text": "If a retail store plans to sell a product to a customer"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 112850.0,
      "end_time": 116910.0,
      "text": "tomorrow, revenue is not earned because again, the business"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 116910.0,
      "end_time": 120060.0,
      "text": "has not as yet done their job."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 120060.0,
      "end_time": 122800.0,
      "text": "Revenues can only be recognized when the business has"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 122800.0,
      "end_time": 127620.0,
      "text": "finished their job, provided the service, or delivered the good."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 127620.0,
      "end_time": 129250.0,
      "text": "Notice the past tense."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 129250.0,
      "end_time": 130870.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s very important with regards"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 130870.0,
      "end_time": 132720.0,
      "text": "to the element, revenue."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 132720.0,
      "end_time": 135380.0,
      "text": "To summarize, revenue is income earned"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 135380.0,
      "end_time": 137780.0,
      "text": "through the day-to-day activities of a business"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 137780.0,
      "end_time": 140900.0,
      "text": "when a service or a good is provided."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 140900.0,
      "end_time": 145600.0,
      "text": "Revenue, earned by providing services or goods."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 145600.0,
      "end_time": 147760.0,
      "text": "Expenses are the cost of the resources that"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 147760.0,
      "end_time": 149620.0,
      "text": "have been used, consumed, or incurred"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 149620.0,
      "end_time": 151400.0,
      "text": "to help generate revenue."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 151400.0,
      "end_time": 154280.0,
      "text": "Expenses are best described through an example."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 154280.0,
      "end_time": 158070.0,
      "text": "If you use gas in a lawnmower when you mow a customer&#39;s lawn,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 158070.0,
      "end_time": 161270.0,
      "text": "then the gas that was consumed during the mowing of the lawn"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 161270.0,
      "end_time": 165130.0,
      "text": "would be an expense, a cost of earning the revenue."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 165130.0,
      "end_time": 166250.0,
      "text": "Why?"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 166250.0,
      "end_time": 168640.0,
      "text": "Because the gas was consumed in order to help"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 168640.0,
      "end_time": 170790.0,
      "text": "generate service revenue."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 170790.0,
      "end_time": 173490.0,
      "text": "Note that the concept of used, consumed, or incurred"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 173490.0,
      "end_time": 176630.0,
      "text": "is important, but so is the fact that these things must have"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 176630.0,
      "end_time": 179160.0,
      "text": "happened to help earn revenue."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 179160.0,
      "end_time": 182310.0,
      "text": "Costs or expenses must be matched to the revenue"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 182310.0,
      "end_time": 184130.0,
      "text": "they help to generate."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 184130.0,
      "end_time": 186700.0,
      "text": "Expenses, costs that have been used,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 186700.0,
      "end_time": 189870.0,
      "text": "consumed, or incurred to help generate revenue."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 189870.0,
      "end_time": 191370.0,
      "text": "Now that you understand the elements"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 191370.0,
      "end_time": 192786.0,
      "text": "that make up the income statement,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 192786.0,
      "end_time": 194360.0,
      "text": "let&#39;s look at the format."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 194360.0,
      "end_time": 196916.0,
      "text": "The format of an income statement is important."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 196916.0,
      "end_time": 198290.0,
      "text": "Note that the heading must always"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 198290.0,
      "end_time": 200690.0,
      "text": "include the business name, the title"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 200690.0,
      "end_time": 203910.0,
      "text": "of the financial statement, and the time period covered."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 203910.0,
      "end_time": 206030.0,
      "text": "Then revenues are listed first."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 206030.0,
      "end_time": 207640.0,
      "text": "If there are multiple revenues, you"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 207640.0,
      "end_time": 209890.0,
      "text": "must list each different type of revenue"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 209890.0,
      "end_time": 214730.0,
      "text": "individually and then show a subtotal called Total Revenues."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 214730.0,
      "end_time": 217330.0,
      "text": "Is there a correct order for revenues?"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 217330.0,
      "end_time": 220680.0,
      "text": "Generally they are always placed in order of magnitude."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 220680.0,
      "end_time": 224140.0,
      "text": "That means from the highest amount to the lowest amount."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 224140.0,
      "end_time": 225290.0,
      "text": "Why?"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 225290.0,
      "end_time": 227660.0,
      "text": "Remember the purpose of financial reporting,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 227660.0,
      "end_time": 230260.0,
      "text": "to provide information for external stakeholders"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 230260.0,
      "end_time": 233280.0,
      "text": "to make resource allocation decisions."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 233280.0,
      "end_time": 236630.0,
      "text": "Therefore, highlighting the largest sources of revenue"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 236630.0,
      "end_time": 240110.0,
      "text": "first helps to make the information more understandable"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 240110.0,
      "end_time": 242460.0,
      "text": "and to increase clarity."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 242460.0,
      "end_time": 244540.0,
      "text": "Expenses are listed next, with a heading"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 244540.0,
      "end_time": 246570.0,
      "text": "called Operating Expenses."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 246570.0,
      "end_time": 249180.0,
      "text": "The order of expenses, similar to revenues,"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 249180.0,
      "end_time": 252020.0,
      "text": "is always from largest to smallest."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 252020.0,
      "end_time": 254100.0,
      "text": "After listing all the expenses, the statement"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 254100.0,
      "end_time": 256279.0,
      "text": "provides a total for all the expenses,"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 256279.0,
      "end_time": 259540.0,
      "text": "excluding income tax expense."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 259540.00000000003,
      "end_time": 263350.0,
      "text": "Next is the subtotal profit before income tax expense,"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 263350.0,
      "end_time": 268130.0,
      "text": "calculated as total revenues minus total operating expenses,"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 268130.0,
      "end_time": 270420.0,
      "text": "then income tax expense as a separate line"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 270420.0,
      "end_time": 274120.0,
      "text": "item before listing the final profit amount."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 274120.0,
      "end_time": 277400.0,
      "text": "Often students place income tax expense in the same listing"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 277400.0,
      "end_time": 279030.0,
      "text": "as operating expenses."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 279030.0,
      "end_time": 281370.0,
      "text": "However, this is incorrect."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 281370.0,
      "end_time": 284640.0,
      "text": "Operating expenses are the costs of running a business"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 284640.0,
      "end_time": 288460.0,
      "text": "and are controllable, for the most part, by the business."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 288460.0,
      "end_time": 292520.0,
      "text": "Income tax expense is prescribed by the CRA, the Canada Revenue"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 292520.0,
      "end_time": 295890.0,
      "text": "Agency, and is not controllable by the business."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 295890.0,
      "end_time": 298190.0,
      "text": "As a consequence, income tax expense"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 298190.0,
      "end_time": 301120.0,
      "text": "must be listed separately."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 301120.0,
      "end_time": 304210.0,
      "text": "What happens if expenses are greater than revenues?"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 304210.0,
      "end_time": 307000.0,
      "text": "Then a net loss amount is provided at the bottom"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 307000.0,
      "end_time": 309640.0,
      "text": "of the income statement."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 309640.0,
      "end_time": 311440.0,
      "text": "The statement we have just developed"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 311440.0,
      "end_time": 313847.0,
      "text": "is called the single-step income statement."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 313847.0,
      "end_time": 315930.0,
      "text": "We&#39;ll be covering a multiple-step income statement"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 315930.0,
      "end_time": 317740.0,
      "text": "in a future video."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 317740.0,
      "end_time": 319627.0,
      "text": "Remember to pause the video to determine"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 319627.0,
      "end_time": 321460.0,
      "text": "your answer to this check your understanding"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 321460.0,
      "end_time": 325900.0,
      "text": "question about the uses of the income statement."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 325900.0,
      "end_time": 328830.0,
      "text": "Bankers are interested in a business&#39; past performance"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 328830.0,
      "end_time": 337130.0,
      "text": "because it helps them-- The answer"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 337130.0,
      "end_time": 341210.0,
      "text": "is not A, determining the amount of debt a business currently"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 341210.0,
      "end_time": 344310.0,
      "text": "has is answered by reviewing the balance sheet."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 344310.0,
      "end_time": 348029.0,
      "text": "The answer is not B, as the current value of a business&#39;"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 348029.0,
      "end_time": 349570.0,
      "text": "property, plant, and equipment is not"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 349570.0,
      "end_time": 353060.0,
      "text": "available on any financial statement that is produced."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 353060.0,
      "end_time": 355650.0,
      "text": "The answer is definitely not D either,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 355650.0,
      "end_time": 357880.0,
      "text": "determining if a business is profitable enough"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 357880.0,
      "end_time": 360900.0,
      "text": "to pay dividends is what owners will use the income"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 360900.0,
      "end_time": 363340.0,
      "text": "statement for, not bankers."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 363340.0,
      "end_time": 365630.0,
      "text": "The correct answer is C, as banks"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 365630.0,
      "end_time": 368360.0,
      "text": "are interested in determining the future profitability"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 368360.0,
      "end_time": 369670.0,
      "text": "of the business."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 369670.0,
      "end_time": 371050.0,
      "text": "Why is this?"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 371050.0,
      "end_time": 373240.0,
      "text": "Because it will help banks predict"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 373240.0,
      "end_time": 375760.0,
      "text": "if the business will repay the loan plus interest"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 375760.0,
      "end_time": 377490.0,
      "text": "in the future."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 377490.0,
      "end_time": 379570.0,
      "text": "Owners use the income statement to determine"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 379570.0,
      "end_time": 381880.0,
      "text": "if the business is profitable and if they will be"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 381880.0,
      "end_time": 384090.0,
      "text": "paid dividends in the future."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 384090.0,
      "end_time": 387650.0,
      "text": "Banks, also called lenders, use the income statement"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 387650.0,
      "end_time": 389500.0,
      "text": "to help them determine if they will"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 389500.0,
      "end_time": 392790.0,
      "text": "fund the business with loans and if the business will,"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 392790.0,
      "end_time": 396610.0,
      "text": "in the future, repay the loan plus interest."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 396610.0,
      "end_time": 398440.0,
      "text": "Other creditors use this statement"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 398440.0,
      "end_time": 400740.0,
      "text": "to figure out if the business will be profitable enough"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 400740.0,
      "end_time": 404290.0,
      "text": "to repay their debts as they come due."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 404290.0,
      "end_time": 406580.0,
      "text": "The long-term survival of any business"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 406580.0,
      "end_time": 409260.0,
      "text": "depends on its ability to produce revenues that are"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 409260.0,
      "end_time": 411310.0,
      "text": "greater than their expenses."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 411310.0,
      "end_time": 414280.0,
      "text": "The income statement, which shows past performance,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 414280.0,
      "end_time": 417790.0,
      "text": "is used by both internal and external stakeholders"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 417790.0,
      "end_time": 422690.0,
      "text": "to predict how profitable the business will be in the future."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 422690.0,
      "end_time": 424210.0,
      "text": "The income statement is a statement"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 424210.0,
      "end_time": 426990.0,
      "text": "that is connected to one other financial statement."
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 426990.0,
      "end_time": 430160.0,
      "text": "The profit or net loss from the income statement"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 430160.0,
      "end_time": 433130.0,
      "text": "is used in the statement of retained earnings."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 433130.0,
      "end_time": 434880.0,
      "text": "Since the profit from the income statement"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 434880.0,
      "end_time": 437280.0,
      "text": "is used in another statement, it is always"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 437280.0,
      "end_time": 440280.0,
      "text": "the first financial statement to be completed."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 440280.0,
      "end_time": 443120.0,
      "text": "The next statement produced is the statement"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 443120.0,
      "end_time": 444870.0,
      "text": "of retained earnings."
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 444870.0,
      "end_time": 448590.0,
      "text": "We&#39;ll be covering that statement in our next video."
    }
  ]
}